Iron Hill Twilight Criterium
description:
Join the party as West Chester celebrates 7 years of racing excitement. Spend the day discovering the charm of historic downtown with its endless array of boutiques, shops and interesting architecture. Enjoy the broad selection of restaurants; no matter whether you\'re looking for - a gourmet dinner or a slice of delicious pizza. Explore the Community Festival; join in the fun at the Market Street Block party. 

Since its inception in 2004, the Iron Hill Twilight Criterium has become one of the most popular cycling events in the area, growing in size and importance year after year. Count on some of the best national and international cyclists to compete.
course: The Iron Hill Twilight Criterium, is a 0.8-mile course of tight turns and straight-aways on the streets of historic downtown West Chester, Pennsylvania. The Start/Finish Line is at the intersection of Gay and High Streets, the home of title sponsor Iron Hill Brewery and Restaurant.
directions:

title: Return of The Great 100
description: This year marks the 40th year since \"The Great 100\" was established. To celebrate we\'re bringing it back. The intention is to, once again, turn this into an annual event open to all. For this year though we\'ll ride it as a Club event. We\'ve updated the ride by showcasing more of the Newton/Ransom area and slightly less of the area north of Shickshinny, as well as adding part of Harvey\'s Lake. The ride now runs in a counterclockwise order which is also different, yet makes a whole lot more sense, especially the long descent from Sweet Valley down to the Susquehanna River at the Twin Cities of Shickshinny / Mocanaqua. Here\'s the link to the map, as well as a printable Cue-Sheet. The ride is free of charge this year.   We have also included a Sag / Support Vehicle for the day. After riding, we\'ve arranged to relax and recover in Nanticoke at TommyBoy\'s Bar & Grill
course: http://ridewithgps.co... The map downloads into your Garmin units. We have now added Rest Area/Support Stops at 3 Volunteer Fire Halls.  Water and Bathrooms will be available at each.  Plus, the LCCC Paramedic Students have generously donated their time and manpower.   BRING YOUR OWN BAG (with your name on it) OF SUPPORT GOODIES (Food, Gels, Powders, etc.) AND LEAVE IT WITH THE SUPPORT STAFF AT THE LCCC PARKING LOT.   YOUR BAG WILL THEN BE TRANSPORTED TO EACH OF THE 3 FIRE HALL Rest Areas for your personal use.  These 3 Rest Stops are located at mile 27 (Newton/Ranson Fire Dept.), mile 48 (Lake Winola Fire Dept., Falls), and 78 (Sweet Valley Fire Dept.)

TOWN HALL CROSS by lamprey systems and St. Lukes H
Murrysville Cyclocross
course: A true east coast cross course with one section of smooth pavement through the S/F area.  Nice mix of off camber turns and open power sections.  There is one mandatory dismount (double barrier) and the spectator favorite Weistertown wall ride/run up.  A designated single side pit will be located adjacent to the S/F.  The course is ~ 2.7km in length, and will be open for inspection during the 15 minutes prior to each event.  No warm-up on the course while a race is in progress.
